node.text:
i’ve been using a lot of time to soak in each moment as it is, when it happens. i’ve focused on the past and held on to things that no longer serve me. grief can come from all kinds of loss but the funniest feeling from grieving is grieving living people who are just no longer in your life. growing apart, one sided relationships, disagreements, change of paths, different mindsets, and there are so many other reasons for this funny feeling. i think it seems inevitable while you have people in your life. they come and they go, you learn from them, sometimes they’re not meant to stay forever and you have to keep carrying on with your journey. what else are you to do but bloom?💐

node.text: i woke up with anxiety about the car. we had just gotten it back from the mechanic. it was making some ticking/rattling sound it didn’t make before, the air bag light keep beeping, it was reading for two different transmission codes and raul had opened the cap to the coolant while it was hot and all the coolant shot out again😣 (pls don’t come at him, because i already did) so after manually bleeding the system myself all night, i went to drive it and that shit just felt like it was ready to fall apart. i had no good gut feeling about it making it another 4.5 hours. i posted the car on craigslist and called some used car places and they wanted to give me $240 for it cause it was a 2002 with 230k miles on it. i had gotten a dm from @joecashmack a few days before about giving us a ride because he was around the area~ i hit him up and asked if that was still on the table. dude wasn’t in the area anymore but still went out of his way to come get us🥺 he had a truck we could fit all our stuff in and we were out! chillin, burnin and vibin the whole way💃 he also owns a dope lil bar in the redwoods a little more north than me, called @applejackslahonda if ya ever wanna go support!🍻 when we went to get our stuff from the car, a lady was checking it out from craigslist and gave me $800 cash for it on the spot. i have been through the damn wringer on this trip but i’m comin’ out shining. i am so thankful for this stupid lil crazy app bringing me to you, @love_missmarie, raul and @joecashmack 🙏🦋 it may have not been the road trip any of us ever had in mind but we did the damn thing. always tell your friends you love them because you never know when it’ll be your last chance. test your drugs if you’re gonna do them because fentanyl is taking over the blackmarket. even in santa cruz, there’s fentanyl in blackmarket prerolled joints. test your shit. i care about you. and i love you. thank you for coming with me on this journey💛🦋

node.text:
we spent another night in reno waiting for the car to get worked on. the front desk dude has been relaying messages instead of letting me talk with the actual technician and he really won’t believe me when i say the cap shot off the coolant reservoir itself. he’s insisting i must have taken it off while it was hot. maybe the last person didn’t screw it in all the way? maybe it actually just had so much pressure it actually shot off? i’m not a mechanic, but i can tell ya, we ain’t touch it. he also is insisting i mixed green coolant with the orange coolant they put in, so i guess the technician didn’t fully flush the car but front desk bb is insisting i mixed them and getting v mad at me🙃 i called a half hour before they closed because i didn’t hear from them and they know we’re camping our way back. i asked if we were getting the car back or if we needed to get a place to stay and he said he didn’t know. so i called 10 mins before and he said i could come get it. then when the uber showed up he called and said nevermind because the tech didn’t think it was safe yet. so they closed, with all out clothes, food, toiletries, kiwis food and everything in our car.🥰🥲 we had to take a lil walmart uber trip to pick up some cheap stuff to be fed & comfy, and booked a motel for the night🛏
this has been such a time of unexpected events and speed bumps that we’re slowly trying to roll over🦋 
hopefully we’ll be outta here today!!🙏

out here tryina trust the process but it’s so hard when everything’s going left. swipe to the last slide to see a video of my car less than an hour after picking it up from the mechanic after getting a new coolant reservoir because mine was cracked🙃 the check engine light came back on, car started acting up again, rpm’s doin weird shit, pulled into auto zone to check the code to see what was up, popped the hood, the top shot off the coolant reservoir and hot coolant was shooting out everywhere. tried to change the thermometer but the parts were all stuck together like cement. 
we’re posted up in a motel for the night. gettin up early with the birds to tow the car back to the mechanic. 
send me the strength to keep a smile on. 
this trip has been so hard, but i’m still here. i made it from omaha to reno with the odds against me. i am strong. i can do anything i put my mind to. i am love. i am not my cars problems. i am not my road trip speed bumps. i am coasting with positive intentions and love in my heart.
